en: beazley_number
collection_history
Bequest of Joseph C. Hoppin. Bought in Athens in 1896. Since the reputed find-spot is Capua, this demonstrates that not everything purchased in Greece was found there; the same is true of Italy.
comparanda
Cf. Cleveland 508.15 (ARV2, 436, 111); and Boston 00.499 (ARV2, 435, 89).
condit
Broken and repaired, with some pieces missing; particularly noticeable are gaps in the body of Dionysos and the heads of three maenads. There is some minor repainting off outlines.
